						               													<description>Command Combat: Civil War - The Battle of Fredericksburg&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Battle of Fredericksburg was one of the most one-sided battles in American history.  Thousands were shot down in front of a stone wall where the dead lay so thick they became a wall of their own.  But it did not have to be that way.  When you play this scenario using the Command Combat system, you can try new strategies.  Play the north or south map, or combine them together.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This scenario was made especially for those looking for a game at Historicon when it was held in the town of Fredericksburg where the actual battle happened.  Play the battle and then see the field where it happened.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
